ìóŸRarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2024-07-27-twin0257.mdŸ@51ddcacf2f2bc7bbbd6ac0f6e4c2b1c4a47f5cdb19254c162e578f1d7be25c57πThis week in Nushell #257ëßNushell⁄®devyn 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13456] fixed 
``keybindings list``
 being empty by default
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13447] fixed 
``$in``
 in range expressions
, bumped Nushell's version (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13439] 1
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13433] 2
), and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13414] updated parsing for unknown args in known externals to be like normal external calls
.
fdncred 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13451] updated release-pkg.nu with a working URL for the less license
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13421] updated query web example due to Wikipedia changes
.
ayax79 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13432] updated the version for nu-ansi-term and reedline
.
NotTheDr01ds 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13429] updated the query-web example to use new chunks
.
f3wenbo 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13417] fixed an output format issue in 
``char --list``
.
IanManske 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13416] fixed setting metadata on byte streams
.
